cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CL, cs.MM 

The paper discusses deep learning in computer vision, specifically unsupervised domain adaptation. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel method for UDA, which falls under the category of machine learning, making cs.LG (Machine Learning) the second likely category. The paper also discusses the importance of preserving discriminative ability for target domain features, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence, making cs.AI the third likely category. The paper also mentions the evaluation procedures for UDA, which falls under the category of natural language processing, making cs.CL (Computation and Language) the fourth likely category. Finally, the paper discusses experiments on various datasets, which falls under the category of multimedia, making cs.MM (Multimedia) the fifth likely category.
